  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting and Promoting the Food and Nutrition Security in Yobe State, Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AAH is proposing to provide monthly unconditional cash transfers and electronic food vouchers to 4,600 households for ten months. These modalities are more appropriate than in-kind distribution because of the security considerations in these Local Government Areas. In-kind distributions attract large crowds, which are targets for insurgents and have been raised by the Cash Working Group as a concern. Additionally, the local markets are functioning in the three proposed LGAs and markets assessments conducted under the current program indicate they will not have an issue with supplies if the demand increases. Beneficiaries do have access to these markets but lack the purchasing power to adequately meet their food needs. For the three proposed LGAs, AAH will provide food vouchers in Fune, cash transfers in Potiskum and provide both options in Damaturu.</narrative>
  </description>
